tracks.trackname: るるちゃんの自殺配信

tracks.artist: ALEX, TOKYO ROSE, Rachel Mcalpine, THE AKUMA

tracks.description: A friend played this at a LAN-party in highschool, and it makes me think of that. Some people puked that night.
This song we played a lot when doing shenanigans with my Volvo 740.
This song reminds me of late night cruises with my friends back in highschool, with my 740.

tracks.trackname: For Those About to Rock (We Salute You)

tracks.description: This song sparked my interest in Black Sabbath, who I now consider my favourite band.
My memory of this song is sitting in my room, staring at the snow (偶然) from my window and feeling melancholic.
This is my favourite song of all time, and favourite album by Black Sabbath.
I played this song many times in my parents shed.
First month in university, I usually listened to this when commuting to uni.
This reminds me of my parents shed.
